Chef solo starter pack

1. Start an EC2 instance running Ubuntu (I used Jaunty 9.04 Server from http://alestic.com/)
   You'll need to edit .ssh/config with the correct user and key for the server, e.g.:

   Host ec2-XX-XX-XX-XX.compute-X.amazonaws.com
     IdentityFile /home/your_name/.ssh/your_private_key
     User root

2. Bootstrap chef:
   $ rake bootstrap SERVER=ec2-XX-XX-XX-XX.compute-X.amazonaws.com

3. Edit your cookbook.

4. Update:
   $ rake update SERVER=ec2-XX-XX-XX-XX.compute-X.amazonaws.com

5. GOTO 3
